# Audric Design System

Source of truth: `apps/web/app/globals.css` + `design_handoff_audric/design_files/colors_and_type.css`.
Prototype reference: `design_handoff_audric/design_files/audric-app-{light,dark}/`.

## Rule 1 — Semantic tokens only, no raw colors

Every color value resolves through a CSS variable. Never use raw hex, never use Tailwind default colors (`red-400`, `gray-500`, `bg-white` outside the documented avatar exception).

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<div className="bg-white border border-gray-200 text-red-500">
<div className="bg-[#F7F7F7] text-[#191919]">
<div style={{ background: '#F7F7F7' }}>

// ✅ GOOD
<div className="bg-surface-page border border-border-subtle text-error-fg">
<div className="bg-surface-card text-fg-primary">
<div style={{ background: 'var(--surface-card)' }}>
```

Available semantic groups (full list in `globals.css`):

- **Surface**: `surface-page` / `surface-card` / `surface-sunken` / `surface-elevated` / `surface-inverse`
- **Foreground**: `fg-primary` / `fg-secondary` / `fg-muted` / `fg-disabled` / `fg-inverse`
- **Border**: `border-default` / `border-subtle` / `border-strong` / `border-focus`
- **Status** (each has `-fg` / `-bg` / `-border` / `-solid`): `success-*` / `warning-*` / `error-*` / `info-*`
- **Accent**: `accent-primary` / `accent-primary-hover` / `accent-primary-bg`
- **Hue palette** (marketing illustrations only): `p400`, `pu500`, `t300`, etc.

## Rule 2 — Theme-flipping tokens for surfaces that swap hierarchy

A handful of surfaces sit at *different* positions in the surface hierarchy between light and dark per the prototype. Use the dedicated theme-flipping token, not a canonical surface token.

| Surface | Token | Light | Dark |
|---|---|---|---|
| Composer / textarea | `surface-input` | card (white) | deepest panel (`#0A0A0A`) |
| Sidebar / nav rail | `surface-nav` | sunken (gray) | lifted card (`#1F1F1F`) |
| Sidebar row hover | `surface-nav-hover` | card | elevated |
| User chat bubble bg | `bubble-user-bg` | near-black | near-black (stable) |
| User chat bubble fg | `bubble-user-fg` | white | white (stable) |

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — sidebar will look identical to page bg in dark
<aside className="bg-surface-sunken">

// ✅ GOOD — sidebar lifts above page in dark per prototype
<aside className="bg-surface-nav">
```

## Rule 3 — Typography uses the ADS ramp + `font-{serif,sans,mono}`

Three semantic font stacks:

- `font-serif` — New York. Headlines, balances, hero numerals.
- `font-sans` — Geist Sans. Default body. Set on `<body>`.
- `font-mono` — Departure Mono. Labels, eyebrows, badges, button text. Always uppercase + tracking.

For full type scale, prefer the `.ads-*` semantic ramp classes (`ads-h1`, `ads-body`, `ads-label-md`, `ads-button-md`, etc.) defined in `globals.css`. Numerals: `.num-display`, `.num-tabular`.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<h1 className="text-3xl font-bold">Balance</h1>

// ✅ GOOD
<h1 className="ads-h1">Balance</h1>
<span className="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.08em] uppercase">Available</span>
```

## Rule 4 — Theming: `data-theme="dark"` only, never branch components

Dark mode is a single `[data-theme="dark"] { ... }` block in `globals.css`. **Never** use `dark:` Tailwind variants. **Never** branch a component on theme. If something looks wrong in dark, fix it at the token layer.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
<div className="bg-white dark:bg-black text-black dark:text-white">
const bg = theme === 'dark' ? 'bg-zinc-900' : 'bg-white';

// ✅ GOOD — tokens flip automatically via [data-theme="dark"] in globals.css
<div className="bg-surface-card text-fg-primary">
```

Light-locked routes (marketing + legal) bypass theming via `apps/web/lib/theme/public-paths.ts`. Themed routes (app shell + utility surfaces like `/verify`, `/auth/callback`, `/pay/[slug]`) get the attribute. Don't add toggle UI outside Settings → Account → Appearance.

## Rule 5 — New screens reference the prototype HTML

Before building a new component or panel, check the corresponding `.jsx` in `design_handoff_audric/design_files/audric-app-{light,dark}/` for the canonical layout, spacing, and tokens. Cite the prototype path in a header comment so the next reader can diff against it:

```tsx
// Visual language matches `design_handoff_audric/design_files/audric-app-light/portfolio.jsx`
// (and `audric-app-dark/portfolio.jsx` for dark variant — same component tree).
export function PortfolioPanel() { ... }
```

## Quick checklist before opening a PR with new UI

- [ ] No raw hex / Tailwind default colors in `className` or inline styles
- [ ] No `dark:` variants
- [ ] Sidebar / composer / chat bubble use the right theme-flipping token
- [ ] Typography uses `.ads-*` ramp classes or `font-{serif,sans,mono}` stacks
- [ ] Header comment cites the design-handoff prototype path
- [ ] Screen renders correctly in both themes (toggle via Settings → Account → Appearance)
